OL,3,CWhisky family lose #1.6 billion but
OL,4,Cstill top Channel Islands' rich list
OL,6,FGlenn Gordon is the Jersey-based
OL,7,Fwhisky baron and chairman of William
OL,8,FGrant & Sons, the company behind
OL,9,FGlenfiddich, Grant's and Drambuie.
OL,11,FGuernsey's John Bloor, of Bloor Homes
OL,12,Fand Triumph Motorcycles, is second on
OL,13,Fthe list, worth just over #3 billion.
OL,15,FOwner of discount store The Range,
OL,16,FChris and Sarah Dawson are the third-
OL,17,Fwealthiest in the Channel Islands,
OL,18,Fwith a joint value of #2.65 billion.
OL,20,FSee below the ten wealthiest people in
OL,21,Fthe Channel Islands 2026:
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G2/6
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
